            <abstract><p>Sends copy of the catalogue of the Royal Botanical Gardens, Naples. Some detail of the garden, which although only recently formed has "every kind of plant", especially those collected by him through his expeditions throughout the kingdom. Offers to send Smith any plants from the catalogue for either his herbarium or botanical gardens in England, and likewise accept any plants in England missing from the catalogue. Sends prospectuses of his "Neapolitan Flora" for circulation.</p></abstract>
